Model Year Start: 2019 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [12/2018 - 07/2020]
Title: EXTERIOR PANELS / TRIM: FRONT BUMPER: DISASSEMBLY; 2019 - 2020 MY Prius [12/2018 - 07/2020]

DISASSEMBLY

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE NO. 3 AIR CLEANER INLET

(a) Remove the screw.

(b) Disengage the 2 claws as shown in the illustration to remove the No. 3 air cleaner inlet.

Remove in this Direction

2. REMOVE FRONT SIDE ULTRASONIC SENSOR (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

3. REMOVE FRONT CORNER ULTRASONIC SENSOR (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

4. REMOVE FRONT CENTER ULTRASONIC SENSOR (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

5. REMOVE FRONT SIDE ULTRASONIC SENSOR RETAINER (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

6. REMOVE FRONT CORNER ULTRASONIC SENSOR RETAINER (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

Click here

7. REMOVE NO. 3 ENGINE ROOM WIRE (w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System)

(a) Disengage the 10 clamps and remove the No. 3 engine room wire.

8. REMOVE MILLIMETER WAVE RADAR SENSOR ASSEMBLY (w/ Pre-collision System)

Click here

9. REMOVE FRONT FENDER LINER RETAINER

(a) Disengage the 2 claws as shown in the illustration to remove the 2 front fender liner retainers.

Remove in this Direction

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

10. REMOVE CONNECTOR COVER (w/o Fog Light)

(a) Disengage the clamp to remove the connector cover.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

11. REMOVE FOG LIGHT ASSEMBLY LH (w/ Fog Light)

Click here

12. REMOVE FOG LIGHT ASSEMBLY RH (w/ Fog Light)

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

13. REMOVE LED ILLUMINATION LIGHT LH (w/ LED Illumination Light)

Click here

14. REMOVE LED ILLUMINATION LIGHT RH (w/ LED Illumination Light)

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

15. REMOVE FOG LIGHT CORD (w/ Fog Light)

(a) w/o LED Illumination Light:

(1) Disengage the 2 clamps to remove the fog light cord.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

(b) w/ LED Illumination Light:

(1) Disengage the clamp to remove the fog light cord.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

16. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER SIDE MOULDING LH (w/o LED Illumination Light)

(a) Remove the 2 screws.

(b) Disengage the 5 claws and 2 guides to remove the front bumper side moulding LH.

17. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER SIDE MOULDING RH (w/o LED Illumination Light)

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

18. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER SIDE MOULDING LH (w/ LED Illumination Light)

(a) Disengage the 5 claws and 2 guides to remove the front bumper side moulding LH.

19. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER SIDE MOULDING RH (w/ LED Illumination Light)

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

20. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION MOUNTING BRACKET

(a) Remove the 2 screws and front bumper extension mounting bracket.

21. REMOVE HOOD TO FRONT END PANEL SEAL

(a) Separate the double-sided tape and disengage the 2 clips to remove the hood to front end panel seal.

Double-sided Tape

-

-

22. REMOVE RADIATOR GRILLE SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Remove the 4 screws and 4 clips.

(b) Disengage the 12 claws and guide as shown in the illustration to remove the radiator grille sub-assembly.

Remove in this Direction

-

-

23. REMOVE RADIATOR GRILLE

(a) Disengage the 6 claws and guide as shown in the illustration to remove the radiator grille.

Remove in this Direction

24. REMOVE RADIATOR GRILLE EMBLEM ASSEMBLY

(a) Remove the 2 screws.

(b) Disengage the 2 claws and guide as shown in the illustration to remove the radiator grille emblem assembly.

Remove in this Direction

25. REMOVE LOWER NO. 1 RADIATOR GRILLE

(a) Remove the 2 screws.

(b) Disengage the 24 claws and 2 guides as shown in the illustration to remove the lower No. 1 radiator grille.

Remove in this Direction

-

-

26. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER HOLE COVER LH

(a) Disengage the 2 claws as shown in the illustration.

*a

Hook

Remove in this Direction

(b) Disengage the hook to remove the front bumper hole cover LH.

27. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER HOLE COVER RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

28. REMOVE NO. 1 FRONT BUMPER PAD

(a) Remove the No. 1 front bumper pad.

HINT:

Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

29. REMOVE NO. 2 FRONT BUMPER PAD

(a) Remove the No. 2 front bumper pad.

30. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER ENERGY ABSORBER

(a) Disengage the 4 guides as shown in the illustration to remove the front bumper energy absorber.

Remove in this Direction

31. REMOVE LOWER FRONT BUMPER ABSORBER

(a) Remove the 3 clips and lower front bumper absorber.

32. REMOVE THERMISTOR ASSEMBLY

Click here

33. REMOVE RADIATOR SHUTTER SUB-ASSEMBLY

Click here

34. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER REINFORCEMENT SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Disengage the 7 clamps.

(b) Remove the 8 bolts.

(c) Disengage the 2 guides to remove the front bumper reinforcement sub-assembly.

35. REMOVE NO. 2 FRONT BUMPER REINFORCEMENT

(a) Remove the 4 nuts and No. 2 front bumper reinforcement.

36. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION LH

(a) Remove the 4 bolts and front bumper extension LH.

37. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER EXTENSION RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

38. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER SIDE SUPPORT LH

(a) Remove the bolt.

(b) Disengage the clip as shown in the illustration.

Remove in this Direction

(c) Disengage the claw as shown in the illustration to remove the front bumper side support LH.

Remove in this Direction

39. REMOVE FRONT BUMPER SIDE SUPPORT RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.
